## 2. Accessibility Blockers (P1)

### index.css (line ~197)
- Focus ring CSS uses invalid property names `ring-color:` and `ring-offset-color:`. These are NOT valid CSS properties and focus indicators are broken for keyboard users. Replace with `--tw-ring-color` and `--tw-ring-offset-color`.

### Devices.tsx, Groups.tsx, Geofences.tsx
- Destructive actions use `window.confirm()` which is inaccessible to screen readers, inconsistent with the design system, and blocks the main thread. Replace with Radix `AlertDialog`.

### AccessibilityPanel.tsx
- Switch controls use `<span>` text instead of `<label htmlFor>` with matching switch IDs. Screen readers cannot associate the label with the control.

### AppSidebar.tsx
- `aria-expanded="true"` is hardcoded on collapsible sections. This does not reflect actual state — screen readers always announce sections as expanded.
- Heading hierarchy issue: uses `<h4>` for sidebar labels when no `<h1>`–`<h3>` precedes them. Use `<p>` with appropriate styling.
- Active nav link lacks `aria-current="page"`.
- Section labels disappear in collapsed mode with no `sr-only` fallback.

### PlatformChart.tsx
- `<tr className="flex ...">` applies flex layout to table rows, breaking native table semantics for assistive technology. Remove flex from table elements or restructure as a non-table layout.

