## 5. Architecture Anti-Patterns (P2)

### Monolithic Files — Decomposition Required
| File | Lines | Action |
|------|-------|--------|
| Applications.tsx | 1,560 | Split into: AndroidAppManager, IosAppManager, GooglePlayIframe, AppStatsSection, AddAppDialog |
| data-table.tsx | 1,377 | Split into: DataTable (orchestrator), DataTableHeader, DataTableBody, DataTablePagination, DataTableToolbar, DataTableFilters, DataTableColumnVisibility, useDataTable hook, types |
| DeviceDetails.tsx | ~2,600 | Split into: DeviceInfoTab, DeviceSecurityTab, DeviceAppsTab, DeviceHardwareTab |
| Profiles.tsx | 789 | Extract platform tabs, stat section, column definitions |
| Enrollment.tsx | 678 | Extract platform-specific enrollment flows into sub-components |

### Missing Patterns
- No `React.lazy()` code splitting — all 21 pages are eagerly imported.
- No global `<Suspense>` fallback for code-split routes.
- No root `<ErrorBoundary>` — unhandled errors white-screen the app.
- No `<React.StrictMode>` wrapper in `main.tsx`.
- `QueryClient` created with no custom defaults (no staleTime, retry, or refetchOnWindowFocus config).
- `EnrollmentGuard` component is a pass-through (`return <>{children}</>`) — dead code.

