## 6. UX Gaps (P2–P3)

### Navigation
- No breadcrumb navigation despite having `breadcrumb.tsx` component. Critical for 4-level-deep routes.
- Header is not sticky — users lose navigation context on long scrollable pages.
- No ⌘K command palette despite `cmdk` being installed as a dependency.
- Sidebar collapsed mode renders empty `<SidebarGroupLabel>` divs for section labels.

### Responsive Design
- Platform tabs use `grid-cols-6` (Devices.tsx, Profiles.tsx) which breaks on mobile.
- Main content padding is fixed `p-6` across all breakpoints.
- No max-width constraint — content runs edge-to-edge on ultrawide monitors.

### Visual Polish
- No page transition animations despite Framer Motion being installed.
- Stat card values are static text with no count-up animation.
- No skeleton loading states deployed on any page.
- Notification badge count is hardcoded `3`, not connected to real data.
- Static notification icon — no visual indication of new notifications.

### Consistency Violations
| Pattern | Correct Usage | Violations |
|---------|--------------|------------|
| AlertDialog for destructive actions | Applications.tsx, WebApplications.tsx | Devices.tsx, Groups.tsx, Geofences.tsx |
| i18n via useLanguage() | Dashboard, Profiles, Enrollment | Groups, Geofences, WebApps, NotFound |
| stat-card design system class | Dashboard, Groups, WebApps | Geofences (raw `<Card>` with hardcoded colors), Profiles (inline cards) |
| Design system color tokens | Most files | Geofences (`bg-blue-100`), Profiles (`text-blue-500`) |
| useToast import path (`@/hooks/use-toast`) | Most files | Groups (`@/components/ui/use-toast`) |
| Responsive platform tabs | Enrollment (`grid-cols-5`) | Devices, Profiles (`grid-cols-6`, non-responsive) |

